{
  "$schema": "./brand.schema.json",
  "meta": {
    "brand_version": 3,
    "note": "The ledger — the shipped identity pinned by ADR-12 (specs/design-direction.md), encoded 2026-07-10 from build.py 0.16.0 (TOKENS_CSS, FAMILY_COLORS, BRAND_MARK, FAVICON) and scripts/icons.py. Values are a faithful transcription. Brand v1 (the dark terminal identity) and the rejected Auditorium proposal live in library/proposals/."
  },
  "identity": {
    "name": "goal-prompts",
    "product_name": "Goal Prompts",
    "tagline": "Turn your coding agent into a senior code auditor.",
    "voice": {
      "tone": "Senior code auditor: technical, rigorous, terminal-native, quiet confidence. Editorial, not promotional.",
      "principles": [
        "evidence not vibes",
        "the page is typeset like the audit report the product sells",
        "warm ink + paper, ruled numbered sections, mono metadata",
        "ONE accent — the auditor's vermilion; family hues survive only as metadata",
        "real report content as the hero artifact",
        "one mark, everywhere: tab, header, home-screen, OG cards all derive from the same geometry"
      ],
      "banned_words": ["revolutionary", "game-changing", "supercharge", "unleash", "blazingly"]
    },
    "signatures": [
      "the 4-bar mark with the tallest bar flagged in vermilion — the finding that matters",
      "the → FILE.md deliverable glyph",
      "ruled, numbered ledger sections"
    ]
  },
  "palette": {
    "themes": {
      "dark": {
        "surfaces": { "ink": "#15120D", "ink-2": "#0F0D09", "panel": "#1C1812", "panel-2": "#252017" },
        "lines": { "line": "#2B2519", "line-2": "#3B3423", "line-3": "#524931" },
        "text": { "text": "#F0EADC", "dim": "#B9B09B", "faint": "#948A72", "body": "#D6CFBE" },
        "controls": { "btn": "#F0EADC", "btn-fg": "#15120D" },
        "accents": { "amber": "#DFA355", "amber-2": "#EFC183", "fc": "#FF6B47" },
        "semantic": { "success": "#5AB380", "warning": "#E09540", "danger": "#F0522E" },
        "severity": { "sev-1": "@danger", "sev-2": "@warning", "sev-3": "#D9C874", "sev-low": "@faint", "sev-fixed": "@success", "sev-ink": "#15120D" },
        "severity_text": { "sev-2-text": "@sev-2", "sev-fixed-text": "@sev-fixed" },
        "aliases": { "good": "@success", "act": "@danger", "up": "@success", "down": "@danger", "meta": "#C9C0AC" }
      },
      "light": {
        "surfaces": { "ink": "#F2EFE6", "ink-2": "#E9E5D6", "panel": "#FAF8F1", "panel-2": "#ECE7D8" },
        "lines": { "line": "#DCD6C3", "line-2": "#C8C1A9", "line-3": "#A69D82" },
        "text": { "text": "#1B1810", "dim": "#524C3C", "faint": "#736B55", "body": "#35302A" },
        "controls": { "btn": "#1B1810", "btn-fg": "#F5F2E9" },
        "accents": { "amber": "#8A651E", "amber-2": "#A47B2B", "fc": "#B93A16" },
        "semantic": { "success": "#207142", "warning": "#8F650E", "danger": "#B02E12" },
        "severity": { "sev-1": "@danger", "sev-2": "@warning", "sev-3": "#736616", "sev-low": "@faint", "sev-fixed": "@success", "sev-ink": "#F5F2E9" },
        "severity_text": { "sev-2-text": "#8F650E", "sev-fixed-text": "#207142" },
        "aliases": { "good": "@success", "act": "@danger", "up": "@success", "down": "@danger", "meta": "#6B6553" }
      }
    },
    "default_theme": "dark",
    "categorical": {
      "Venture": "#C878F0", "Product": "#E8B44C", "Quality": "#E8705F",
      "Speed": "#4D9FFF", "Trust": "#52C280", "Growth": "#A98CF5",
      "Team": "#3FC1C9", "Clarity": "#9AD4E8", "Design": "#5CE8A0",
      "Data": "#F0904A", "Ops": "#B4C64A", "Subtract": "#E87FB0",
      "Meta": "#C4CBD8", "Act": "#E84C3D", "Agent": "#8B7CF8",
      "Automation": "#E8DE5A", "AI-UX": "#F06FD8", "Compliance": "#8892B0",
      "API": "#36B3EC", "Reliability": "#8CA878", "AI-Ethics": "#6E8AF0",
      "Build": "#8CD94C", "Mission": "#AA7A55"
    },
    "categorical_prefix": "f-",
    "categorical_var": "fc",
    "categorical_mix": { "light": { "toward": "black", "percent": 58 } },
    "notes": {
      "ink": "the ledger palette (specs/design-direction.md): warm ink + paper + ONE\n     accent — the auditor's vermilion. Family hues survive only as metadata.",
      "sev-1": "one severity ramp (COLOR C6/R64), re-keyed onto the ledger palette — the\n     hero's S2 chip and Studio's .c-s* both consume these. --sev-3 sits\n     deliberately off the ledger amber; --sev-ink is the on-chip ink, AA 4.5+\n     on --sev-2 in each theme (SeverityContrastTests pins both).",
      "sev-2-text": "text-on-panel variants for the two ramp stops (Studio's .c-s2/.c-fixed):\n     dark aliases the fills (they already read as text there); light re-keys\n     them onto the paper surfaces.",
      "good": "Primary-action colour convention (HIERARCHY F6): the accent --fc is the\n     *browse/navigate* primary; --act (red) is the *commit / act-adjacent*\n     primary — the Studio Fixer button, the Act family. In the ledger system\n     both live in the vermilion family on purpose: red = flagged / act.",
      "w-page": "container + rhythm scale (LAYOUT L1/T4 — one source; @media can't take var() so breakpoints stay literal)",
      "s1": "spacing scale — 4pt base (LAYOUT L2/L4/L6); map off-grid values (9,7,22…) onto it"
    }
  },
  "contrast": {
    "surfaces": ["ink", "ink-2", "panel", "panel-2"],
    "text_min": { "text": 4.5, "body": 4.5, "dim": 4.5, "faint": 3.0 },
    "accents": ["amber", "fc", "success", "warning", "danger", "meta", "sev-3"],
    "accents_min": 3.0,
    "categorical_min": 3.0,
    "categorical_surfaces": ["ink", "panel", "panel-2"],
    "note": "Seeded at the ledger's shipped floors. categorical_surfaces mirrors the surface set tests/test_build.py TokensTests pins (panel, ink, panel-2); the light 58% mix was chosen by that gate (62% left Automation at 2.9:1 on panel-2)."
  },
  "type": {
    "faces": [
      {
        "role": "display",
        "family": "Schibsted Grotesk",
        "css_name": "Schib",
        "license": "OFL-1.1",
        "files": [
          { "path": "fonts/schibstedgrotesk-latin-var.woff2", "weight": "400 800", "style": "normal" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "role": "sans",
        "family": "IBM Plex Sans",
        "css_name": "PSans",
        "license": "OFL-1.1",
        "files": [
          { "path": "fonts/plexsans-latin-400.woff2", "weight": "400", "style": "normal" },
          { "path": "fonts/plexsans-latin-600.woff2", "weight": "600", "style": "normal" }
        ]
      },
      {
        "role": "mono",
        "family": "IBM Plex Mono",
        "css_name": "IBM Plex Mono",
        "license": "OFL-1.1",
        "files": [
          { "path": "fonts/plexmono-latin-400.woff2", "weight": "400", "style": "normal" },
          { "path": "fonts/plexmono-latin-600.woff2", "weight": "600", "style": "normal" }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "stacks": {
      "disp": "'Schib','PSans',system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif",
      "sans": "'PSans',system-ui,-apple-system,'Segoe UI',Roboto,sans-serif",
      "mono": "'IBM Plex Mono',ui-monospace,'SF Mono',Menlo,Consolas,monospace"
    },
    "preload": [
      "fonts/schibstedgrotesk-latin-var.woff2",
      "fonts/plexsans-latin-400.woff2",
      "fonts/plexmono-latin-400.woff2"
    ]
  },
  "space": {
    "layout": { "w-page": "1120px", "w-doc": "960px", "w-read": "760px", "gutter": "24px", "lh-body": "1.6" },
    "scale": { "s1": "4px", "s2": "8px", "s3": "12px", "s4": "16px", "s5": "24px", "s6": "32px", "s7": "40px", "s8": "48px", "s9": "64px" },
    "sections": { "section": "64px", "section-tight": "48px" }
  },
  "radii": { "r-sm": "2px", "r-md": "3px", "r-pill": "999px", "radius": "2px" },
  "motion": {
    "durations": { "press": ".1s", "state": ".15s", "move": ".2s", "enter": ".4s" },
    "easings": { "default": "ease", "enter": "cubic-bezier(.2,.7,.3,1)" },
    "note": "motion (STATES §4) — the one vocabulary already in use, named",
    "reduced_motion": "none"
  },
  "mark": {
    "viewbox": 24,
    "class": "mark",
    "size": 24,
    "elements": [
      { "type": "rect", "x": 1, "y": 9, "w": 3.4, "h": 9, "rx": 0.8, "fill": "currentColor", "solid": "#F0EADC" },
      { "type": "rect", "x": 6.9, "y": 3, "w": 3.4, "h": 15, "rx": 0.8, "fill": "var(--fc,#C8451F)", "solid": "#FF6B47" },
      { "type": "rect", "x": 12.8, "y": 7, "w": 3.4, "h": 11, "rx": 0.8, "fill": "currentColor", "solid": "#F0EADC" },
      { "type": "rect", "x": 18.7, "y": 12, "w": 3.4, "h": 6, "rx": 0.8, "fill": "currentColor", "solid": "#F0EADC" }
    ],
    "note": "Four audit bars, three in ink (currentColor, so it re-keys with the theme) and the tallest flagged in the accent — 'the finding that matters'. One accent, not four hues (specs/design-direction.md). The favicon/PNG icons render the `solid` fills on the dark rounded square.",
    "favicon": { "viewbox": 64, "bg": "#15120D", "bg_radius": 6, "tx": 10, "ty": 9.2, "scale": 1.9 }
  },
  "host": {
    "integration": "python-import",
    "tokens_out": "tokens.css",
    "fonts_dir": "fonts",
    "fonts_url": "/fonts/",
    "pages_to_shoot": ["/", "/studio.html", "/vitals.html", "/b/01.html", "/p/facelift.html"],
    "themes_to_shoot": ["dark", "light"],
    "theme_storage_key": "gp-theme",
    "extra_css": [
      "button:active{transform:scale(.97)}",
      "button:disabled,[aria-disabled=\"true\"]{opacity:.5;cursor:not-allowed}"
    ],
    "hex_lint": {
      "files": ["template.html", "studio.html", "vitals.html"],
      "allow": []
    }
  }
}
